member.example:
This sample shows how to call GetAssessmentJobRuleAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var endpoint = new Uri("<https://my-service.azure.com>");
var client = new AssessmentJobRuleClient(endpoint, credential);

Response response = await client.GetAssessmentJobRuleAsync("<accountId>", "<assetId>", "<assessmentId>");

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.ToString());

